ding and had suffered a damaged wing.</p> <p>The second test occurred on 22 May, Martin Luis Gomez, Facebook’s director of aeronautical platforms, said in a blog post. The aircraft flew for an hour and 46 minutes before landing near Yuma, Arizona, with only “a few minor, easily-repairable dings,” he said.</p> <p>Facebook engineers had added spoilers to the aircraft’s wings to increase drag and reduce lift during the landing approach, Gomez said.</p>
